summary: Cristian Rosasco is 34 years old, living in Rome, prefers he/him pronouns, and resembles Chris Evans. Family was the backbone of...
caption:
Cristian Rosasco is 34 years old, living in Rome, prefers he/him pronouns, and resembles Chris Evans.

Family was the backbone of the Rosasco clan – a large, boisterous group of beings who found themselves closely threaded together in the streets of Rome. It was almost cliché, really, the fact that they could be comparable to the portrayal of loud and crazy Italian families in Hollywood movies, and it was something they all embraced entirely. Gio and Adele found their hands full with five pairs of feet constantly running around, and while they were all certainly little Rosascos they were all very different. It was exhausting to say the least, to have to nurture varying degrees of interests and hobbies when it was spread out in five directions. One was athletic, the other a musician who took to several instruments, and the twins? Well, they were twins. Cristian, the second oldest and a man who took his role as the big brother seriously, enjoyed the comfort of home and activities that weren’t as aggressive as his older sister’s soccer games or as loud as Nico’s affection for the drums. A coloring book in the backyard was much more up his alley, or helping his mother prepare dinner while his dad herded the children into the bathroom to clean up before they sat down at the table. He had a heart of gold, he was often told, and it only grew the older he got.

There was just the smallest chip in it however, the tiniest fracture cracking from the inside out when Gio Rosasco succumbed to a heart infection that blindsided them all. With his general nature making him reach a level of maturity most ten year olds didn’t possess, Cristian knew what kind of responsibility was about to fall of his shoulders. He was now the man of the house, the protector and provider, but it wasn’t too far of a step from the caring big brother persona he put forward already so the transition wasn’t as difficult as it could have been. It was hard, doing so while dealing with the death of his father, but Cristian knew that keeping the family together was what was needed while they headed into their new life without Gio. Despite wanting to withdraw into himself for a few days, wanting nothing more than to learn how to deal with the new emptiness he was feeling, Cristian made sure that things functioned as they always had. It became easier as the years went on, him doing everything he could for his mother and giving his siblings the encouragement that he knew his father would have handed out so easily. He was suddenly the one at his sister’s games cheering her on from the stands, the one who listened to all of Nico’s new sounds and practiced with him despite having no sense of rhythm himself. When Bianca, the rough and rowdy playful twin when compared to her twin sister, broke her ankle he was the one who piggybacked her all the way to the hospital when they remember his mother had gone out for groceries and hadn’t returned yet. The role of guardian came naturally to him, and it was that role that followed him well into his thirties.

It only seemed like it was a matter of time before the protector side of him translated into his life path, Cristian finding himself teaching kindergarten at Greenwood Garden School. It didn’t come as a surprise that, that was where he had found himself, him always having an exceptional ability to connect with children even when he was a child himself. Being a supporter, a teacher, a trustworthy guardian in the lives of the kids he saw through the years was the position he was meant to have. His siblings had outgrown their dependency on him as they blossomed into their own adulthood, and while they knew he would be there for them unconditionally they didn’t look up to him in the same way they once had. Fulfilment was what Cristian had found in becoming a teacher, happy to know that he was playing a vital role in the development of the children that came through his classroom. His already big family became even larger with every new school year, and he couldn’t ask for more.

✥ Find Cristian
